{"questionId":"22435719","questionHtml":"<p>State a conclusion to the test. Give a reason for your answer.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>22</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>5483</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>9</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>49</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp;<strong>OR&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong> <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>000155837</mn><mo>…</mo><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn><mo>.</mo><mn>05</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <strong><em>R1</em></strong></p>\n<p>(there is sufficient evidence to) reject the null hypothesis&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; <em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Do not award <em><strong>R0A1</strong></em>.</p>\n<p>Accept “accept the alternative hypothesis”.</p>\n<p>Their conclusion must be consistent with their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>χ</mi><mi>calc</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math> (or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value) and their hypothesis.</p>\n<p>Accept <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>χ</mi><mi>calc</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup><mo>&gt;</mo><msubsup><mi>χ</mi><mi>crit</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi><mo>&lt;</mo></math>sig level provided their <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msubsup><mi>χ</mi><mi>calc</mi><mn>2</mn></msubsup></math> value or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>p</mi></math>-value is seen.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align:right;\"><strong><em>[2 marks]</em></strong></p>","meta":{"questionId":"22435719","referenceCode":"24M.1.SL.TZ2.3bii","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"State a conclusion to the test. Give a reason for your answer.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"ii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 4—Statistics and probability","Topic 4—Statistics and probability","SL 4.11—Expected, observed, hypotheses, chi squared, gof, t-test"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}